description.narrative:
The Digital Defenders Partnership's overall objective for the coming strategic period is that Human Rights Defenders(HRDs) remain resilient to closing civic space and continue to effectively use the internet and information and communications technology to promote and defend human rights.
DDP has formulated three strategic goals that contribute towards acheving the overall objective:
1. Provide timely, flexible and holistic emergency response resources to reduce the impactor risk of digital attacks against human rights defenders;
2. Strengthen awareness and capacities for sustainable and effective responses to digital threats among human rights defenders at risk;
3. Develop, maintain, and support accessible, collaborative, resilient and responsive networks of expertise and support for human rights defenders under digital threat.
